<div class="container">
<h2>About the Online Ecommerce Application</h2>
<p>
    This Online Ecommerce Application is a simple yet functional web-based shopping system 
    built using <strong>Advanced Java (JSP, Servlets, JDBC)</strong> without any external frameworks. 
    The purpose of this project is to demonstrate how a dynamic web application works internally — 
    from handling user authentication to managing products and processing user actions through 
    servlets and database connectivity.
</p>

<p>
    The application provides essential ecommerce features such as user registration, login, 
    session-based authentication, product listing, and a shopping cart mechanism. 
    Each operation is handled through dedicated servlets which interact with the database 
    using DAO classes, ensuring clean separation of concerns and easy maintenance.
</p>

<p>
    This project is ideal for beginners who want to understand how web applications work behind the scenes. 
    It focuses entirely on core technologies like JSP for UI, Servlets for backend logic, JDBC for database 
    operations, and MySQL for data storage. By learning this project, you develop a solid understanding 
    of request handling, session management, MVC architecture, and relational database integration 
    without relying on heavy frameworks.
</p>

<p>
    Explore the features, experiment with the modules, and enhance it further as you grow in your 
    Java Web Development journey. This application forms a strong foundation for transitioning into 
    modern frameworks like Spring Boot, Hibernate, and Angular or React later.
</p>
</div>
